- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of machine learning and normalization techniques to assist with engine diagnosis falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the diagnosis of complex systems (aircraft gas turbine engines) and the development of a software tool to assist with this task. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the development of a software tool for assisting technicians with the interpretation of sensor data. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): Although the paper does not explicitly mention the use of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms, these techniques are commonly used in machine learning and could potentially be applied to this problem.
